quest_title: A 40kg boy jump form 4m on plate form mounted with spring. As the springs compress, the platform is pushed down by 0.2m below its initial position. The speed of boy when platform depressed by 0.1m is
explanation_txt:
\(\begin{aligned} \operatorname{mg}(\mathrm{h}+\mathrm{r})=& 1 / 2 \mathrm{kr}^{2} \\ \text { or, } \mathrm{k} &=\cfrac{2 \times 40 \times 10(4+0.2)}{0.2^{2}} \\ &=84000 \mathrm{N} / \mathrm{m} \end{aligned}\)

\(\mathrm{k}=\mathrm{m} \omega^{2}\)
\(\therefore \omega=\sqrt{\cfrac{k}{m}}=\sqrt{\cfrac{8400}{40}}=45.8 \mathrm{rad} / \mathrm{s}\)
\(\therefore \mathrm{v}=\omega \sqrt{r^{2}-y^{2}}\)

Considering \( 2x^2 - 7x - 30 = 0 \), the roots are:

\[ x = \cfrac{7 \pm \sqrt{49+240}}{4} = \cfrac{7 \pm 17}{4} = 6 \, or, \, -\cfrac{10}{4} \]

\( y-y_1 = - \cfrac{y_1}{2a} (x-x_1) \)

So the normal is:

\(\begin{array} { l } { y - a = \cfrac { - a } { 2 a } \left( x - \cfrac { a } { 4 } \right) } \\ { \Rightarrow 2 y + x = 2 a + \cfrac { a } { 4 } = \cfrac { 9 a } { 4 } \Rightarrow 2 y + x - \cfrac { 9 a } { 4 } = 0 } \\ { \text { i.e., } 4 x + 8 y - 9 a = 0 } \end{array}\)
